sentences: Elisabeth Schumann (13 June 1888 – 23 April 1952) was a German soprano who sang in opera, operetta, oratorio, and lieder.
She made her stage debut in Hamburg in 1909.
She remained at the Hamburg State Opera until 1919, also singing during the 1914/1915 season at the Metropolitan Opera, New York.

From 1919 until 1938, she was a star of the Vienna State Opera.

The conductor Karl Alwin was her second husband from 1920 until 1938.

sentences: She was closely connected with Richard Strauss, Otto Klemperer, Lotte Lehmann, Bruno Walter, Wilhelm Furtwängler, and other leading musicians of the first half of the 20th century.
In a career spanning 28 years, Schumann sang 91 roles.
Her debut role was the Shepherd Boy in Tannhäuser on 2 September 1909 in Hamburg; on 1 November 1937 her last role was the First Flower maiden in Parsifal in Vienna.
